Engineering Note 850820-1
Conversion of DSI-32 to take NS32016.

The  NS32016 is a 100% instruction set compatible  microprocessor 
to the NS32032.  The NS32016 has a 32 bit wide internal data path 
and  a 16 bit external data path,  while the NS32032 has both  32 
bit wide internal and external data paths.
The measured performance degradation in using the NS32016 instead 
of the NS32032 on the DSI-32 board is roughly 30%.
Also  the use of the NS32016 CPU excludes the later  installation 
of  the NS32082 memory management unit in the DSI-32.  This means 
that  UNIX can not then be run on the board.  For real  time  and 
single user applications this is not a problem.

To  install the NS32016 on the DSI-32 the following steps need to 
be followed.

1) Remove the NS32032 CPU from the DSI-32 board.  The NS32032  is 
   the 68 chip in the LCC socket in the center of the board.

2) Insert the NS32016 CPU in the 48 pin socket to the left of the 
   LCC socket.

